news.title: Rajasthan housing board tweaks law for offering turnkey houses to owners
news.para: Now, whatever new independent houses or multi-storeyed flats will be built by the Housing Board for different income groups, they will be built on the basis of these new types of designs.

news.title: Dharwad: HDMC mulls bringing two lakh hidden properties under ambit of civic tax
news.para: Opening the discussion on increasing the revenue, senior corporator Veeranna Savadi fumed at officials for their poor show in tax collection.

news.title: CRDA Act amendment to make use of PMAY: Andhra Pradesh government to HC
news.para: Arguing on behalf of the state government, additional advocate general P Sudhakar Reddy said the Union government will give funds for construction of houses and the state government intends to construct houses apart from giving house sites to the landless poor in capital city.

news.title: Noida: There are over 300 flats in sector 117, but no park to visit
news.para: Taking cognisance of the residents' demand, Noida authority CEO Ritu Maheshwari directed the chief architect planner (CAP) for a detailed report of the issue and the area and assured action based on the report.

news.title: Rajasthan government lowers max height cap for buildings on small plots
news.para: Effectively these changes concentrated on reducing the maximum permissible limit of heights for new buildings to be built on small plots measuring up to 750 square metre.

news.title: Bulldozers at Raisina Hills, two years after NGT order to restore forest
news.para: Gurgaon’s divisional forest officer Rajiv Tejyan said that a total of 52 violations were reported in areas protected under sections 4 and 5 of the Punjab Land Preservation Act (PLPA), 1900. “Showcause notices have been issued to all the violators. More demolitions are to follow in the coming days.”

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Builder gets 26,888 sq meters of Parsik Hill slope for just Rs 100 a year
news.para: In another RTI response, the state environment department has confirmed to NatConnect that no environmental clearance has been obtained for digging the hill in the recent past.

news.title: Architects seek security for whistleblower who exposed RERA scam in Kalyan & Dombivli
news.para: The Indian Institute of Architect Association demanded that Thane police provide police protection to Patil. They said his life was in danger for exposing the scam in which many influential people are involved.

news.title: Noida: 30 farmhouses razed in one day on Yamuna floodplains
news.para: Last Monday, the Authority had asked lekhpals and the civil department to submit a report on encroachments in the Hindon and Yamuna floodplains. Officials said the drive would continue in the coming days.

news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai rises 15% to 8,756 units in November
news.para: Growth in property sale registrations in Mumbai continues to remain robust with some moderation recorded in the recent months, the consultant said.

news.title: ABSA Fashions leases 18 floors office in Mumbai
news.para: The company will be paying rentals of over Rs 60 crore for this office space spread over more than 102,000 sq ft through the lease term excluding the escalation. As per the agreement, the rentals will see a 12% escalation after the first 36 months.

news.title: China property stocks surge on fundraising support
news.para: The move will make it easier for developers to obtain fresh funding, analysts said, but reviving demand from homebuyers would remain challenging amid persisting COVID-19 curbs that have triggered rare street protests across many Chinese cities.

news.title: Mortgage approvals in Britain hit lowest since June 2020
news.para: Britain's housing market is showing clear signs of slowing, with various gauges of house prices now showing cooling inflation after rapid growth during the pandemic.

news.title: Shimao Group Holdings to raise funds as Beijing lifts equity sales ban
news.para: Shimao's fundraising target will not exceed 30% of the current capital base, it said. Based on the developer's market value of 11.3 billion yuan ($1.58 billion) on Wednesday the deal size could be up to $474 million.

news.title: IFC partially exits Puravankara's Bengaluru project
news.para: The exit — from 1.4 million square feet plotted development project spread over 60 acres — was at an internal rate of return of 20%. The project is at an advanced stage of completion with 80% of the houses sold out. IFC had invested Rs 157 crore in the project over the last two years.
